### 3c. Provider Docs (user-facing): `packages/web/src/content/docs/providers.mdx`

**Path:** `/Users/christopherdavid/work/projects/repos/opencode/packages/web/src/content/docs/providers.mdx`

This is the comprehensive user-facing documentation (2465 lines). The **Custom provider** section (lines 2323-2449) is the most relevant -- it documents the exact JSON format for adding any OpenAI-compatible provider:

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://opencode.ai/config.json",
  "provider": {
    "myprovider": {
      "npm": "@ai-sdk/openai-compatible",
      "name": "My AI Provider Display Name",
      "options": {
        "baseURL": "https://api.myprovider.com/v1",
        "apiKey": "{env:MY_API_KEY}",
        "headers": {
          "Authorization": "Bearer custom-token"
        }
      },
      "models": {
        "my-model-name": {
          "name": "My Model Display Name",
          "limit": {
            "context": 200000,
            "output": 65536
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Key documentation details from the custom provider section:

- **`npm`**: Use `"@ai-sdk/openai-compatible"` for `/v1/chat/completions` endpoints; use `"@ai-sdk/openai"` for `/v1/responses` endpoints
- **`options.baseURL`**: The API endpoint URL (must end in `/v1` for OpenAI-compatible)
- **`options.apiKey`**: Can reference env vars via the `{env:VAR_NAME}` syntax
- **`options.headers`**: Custom headers sent with every request
- **`models.<id>.name`**: Display name for each model
- **`models.<id>.limit.context`**: Max input tokens
- **`models.<id>.limit.output`**: Max output tokens
- The provider ID used in `/connect` must match the key in the config's `provider` object

